#: src/pages/docs/OverviewPage.tsx:65
msgid "<0>Composite once, fan out many.</0> The canvas is encoded once per rendition and the same packets feed every transport, rather than re-encoding per destination."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/OverviewPage.tsx:51
msgid "<0>Continuous output.</0> One monotonic output clock produces a valid, correctly-timestamped frame every tick, independent of any input."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/OverviewPage.tsx:72
msgid "<0>Control never back-pressures the engine.</0> The management API, realtime streams, and preview are best-effort and physically incapable of stalling the output path."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:190
msgid "<0>fit</0> controls scaling: <1>fill</1>, <2>contain</2>, <3>cover</3>, <4>none</4>, or <5>scale_down</5>."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:69
msgid "<0>HLS / file output.</0> Writes a playlist and segments to disk. This is the path the quick-start uses and that works today."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/OverviewPage.tsx:58
msgid "<0>Last-good-frame resilience.</0> Each tile rides a live / stale / reconnecting / no-signal state machine; a failing input cannot block the compositor."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:88
msgid "<0>Live RTSP / NDI / RTMP / SRT servers and push.</0> The network output servers are not yet wired into the run command."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:79
msgid "<0>Low-latency HLS.</0> Partial-segment HLS for lower glass-to-glass latency."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ApiPage.tsx:114
msgid "<0>Server-Sent Events</0> (fallback) at <1>/api/v1/events</1> — one-way, for environments where a WebSocket cannot be used."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ApiPage.tsx:108
msgid "<0>WebSocket</0> (primary) at <1>/api/v1/ws</1> — bidirectional, used for the live UI."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:119
msgid "A CSS-grid layout with <0>columns</0> and <1>rows</1> track lists (<2>fr</2> / <3>px</3> / <4>%</4>), a <5>gap</5>, and an <6>areas</6> map that names where each cell sits."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:25
msgid "A layout decides where every tile sits on the canvas. Use a factory preset (such as 2x2 or 1+5), a CSS-grid with named areas and fractional tracks, or absolute normalized rectangles for full control. A cell's fit mode controls how a source is scaled into its tile — contain to letterbox, cover to crop and fill, or fill to stretch."
msgstr ""

#: src/layout/components/validationMessages.tsx:18
msgid "A layout name is required."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:24
msgid "A Multiview deployment is one declarative document. It is authored as TOML and round-trips losslessly to JSON (the API wire form)."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:113
msgid "A named factory arrangement: <0>2x2</0>, <1>3x3</1>, <2>1+5</2>, or <3>pip</3>."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:203
msgid "A per-cell <0>qos</0> block sets a degradation <1>priority</1> and strategy, so the engine sheds the cheapest tiles first under load before touching the program output."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:124
msgid "A salvo is a named, atomically-applied recall. One salvo can switch the layout, rebind sources into cells, set tally colors, and update under-monitor display text — all at once — so an operator can move a whole arrangement (say, a VTR review setup) with a single action instead of a series of separate edits."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ComposePage.tsx:39
msgid "A small RTSP server that, on start, runs ffmpeg to publish a synthetic test pattern with a sine-wave audio tone to <0>rtsp://testsrc:8554/test</0>."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/FeaturesPage.tsx:38
msgid "A source is a managed input. Each one owns its ingest, decode, color handling, and reconnect behaviour, and is referenced by tiles via a stable id. Supported kinds include RTSP, HLS, MPEG-TS, SRT, RTMP, NDI, file, and a built-in synthetic test pattern. When a source stops delivering frames, its tile holds the last good frame and moves through a clear state machine — live, stale, reconnecting, no-signal — while the engine reconnects without disturbing the rest of the wall."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ComposePage.tsx:53
msgid "A tiny nginx that serves the HLS volume over HTTP so you can open the stream in a player at <0>http://localhost:8888/multiview.m3u8</0>."
msgstr ""

