msgid "Each <0>[[outputs]]</0> entry is one sink, tagged by <1>kind</1>. The canvas is composited and encoded once, then fanned out to every output. Today, file-based HLS output works; the live network output servers are on the roadmap (see the feature guide)."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:222
msgid "Each <0>[[overlays]]</0> entry attaches a layer to the whole <1>canvas</1> or to a single cell. Common kinds are <2>clock</2>, <3>label</3>, and <4>tally_border</4>. Kind-specific parameters (such as a clock <5>format</5>) sit alongside the common fields and round-trip losslessly."
msgstr ""

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:137
msgid "Each <0>[[sources]]</0> entry is a managed input with a stable <1>id</1>, an optional <2>display_name</2>, and a <3>kind</3> that selects the transport. The network kinds carry a <4>url</4>; NDI binds by <5>name</5>; file inputs use a <6>path</6>; <7>test</7> is a built-in synthetic pattern with no parameters."
msgstr ""

